    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for a cheap, dependable runaround without spending a fortune? This car isn\u2019t perfect, but it\u2019s an honest budget-friendly vehicle with plenty of life left for the right buyer. Great as a first car, commuter, or spare set of wheels. It shows its age and has its rough spots, but if you want straightforward value and a car that can still do the job, this one is well worth a look. Priced to sell and represented honestly.",
      "price": 6900.0,
      "reputation": 0.9,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 46
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid budget-friendly driver/project with strong bones and plenty of usable life left. The powertrain starts, runs, and moves out with respectable pull, and the chassis feels like a good candidate for someone who wants dependable basic transportation or a platform to sort and improve over time. Not a cosmetic queen, but it offers honest utility, mechanical simplicity, and real value for a buyer who appreciates function over flash. A practical pickup for a daily beater, backup vehicle, or weekend wrenching project.",
      "price": 5900.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 46
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
